      <div class="rows container">
              <div class="row row1">
                <span><img class="img_1" src="/infoPage/img/checklist.png" /></span>
                <span class="txt">
                  <h4 class="">Paper-based Systems</h4>
                  <p>
                    Health records are currently dominated by a paper-based phenomenon
                    that is negatively impacting patient medical record accessibility
                    and tracking for administrative and medical purposes.
                  </p>
                </span>
                <span class="link"><a href="#">learn more</a></span>
              </div>
              <div class="row row2">
                <span><img class="img_1" src="/infoPage/img/error.png" /></span>
                <span class="txt">
                  <h4 class="">Compliance Issues</h4>
                  <p class="">
                    Medical records are currently managed physically, which is drastically affecting compliance and causing revenue loss for the healthcare organization. The constantly evolving regulatory changes make it difficult for human efforts.</p>
                </span>
                <span class="link"><a href="#">learn more</a></span>
              </div>
              <div class="row row3">
                <span><img class="img_1" src="/infoPage/img/security-breach.png" /></span>
                <span class="txt">
                  <h4 class="">Data Breaches</h4>
                  <p class="">
                    Medical records can now be accessed on multiple devices by
                    authorized medical staff and personnel, which is causing breaches
                    in data and causing sensitive patient information to be misused.
                  </p>
                </span>
                <span class="link"><a href="#">learn more</a></span>
              </div>
              <div class="row row4">
                <span><img class="img_1" src="/infoPage/img/id-card.png" /></span>
                <span class="txt">
                  <h4 class="">Medical Identity Theft</h4>
                  <p class="">
                    Patient records and their health information is prone to identity
                    theft, wherein a third party uses the patient information to
                    access medical products and can alter this information. This
                    alteration can result in improper medical treatment.
                  </p>
                </span>
                <span class="link"><a href="#">learn more</a></span>
              </div>
              <div class="row row5">
                <span><img class="img_1" src="/infoPage/img/shield.png" /></span>
                <span class="txt">
                  <h4 class="">Safe Data Storage</h4>
                  <p class="">
                    Data storage that is free of risks continues to be a struggle for
                    healthcare organizations due to the increasing number of hacks and
                    breaches. Storing volumes of patient data on a platform that is
                    secure is therefore a pressing need.
                  </p>
                </span>
                <span class="link"><a href="#">learn more</a></span>
              </div>
              <div class="row row6">
                <span><img class="img_1" src="/infoPage/img/consumer-behavior.png" /></span>
                <span class="txt">
                  <h4 class="">Consumer Expectation</h4>
                  <p class="">
                    With the initiation of electronic health records, patients now
                    have access to medical information and their expectations to
                    control this information is steadily increasing. This expectation
                    is poised to rise as medical record evolve in the digital world.
                  </p>
                </span>
